Omenka Uzoma Day aka Uzo has expressed gratitude to the Minister of Information, Alhaji Lai Mohammed for his support following the appreciation of his song, Nigeria. Uzo, who is currently on a tour of the United Kingdom with his band, made this known in a telephone chat with The Nation.   Wife to donate kidney to Eedris Abdulkareem     ‘Peter Obi can only win on Twitter’     Mixed reactions over PSquare’s comeback songs   He said, “I cannot thank the honourable minister enough for his support. Everywhere I have been performing; Nigerians relate to the song and see themselves as one. I can tell you that the video of the song shot at the National Theatre with the huge help of the GM/CEO Professor Sunday Ododo and the staff of the National Theatre in itself is greatly uniting and projecting Nigeria positively and culturally. Also, I will be available with my crew for the grand opening of the National Theatre.” Uzo was the former manager of the late reggae icon, Majek Fashek, who passed away in 2020.